{
  "texts": [
    "The fact that you had to go only a little further forward with mechanical calculation to win nearly every time, took everyone by surprise and that is why Dreyfus was not as wrong as it appears since he was basing his arguments on what was known at the time about human and computer chess players.",
    "Since then, however, all this has been overwhelmed by 'NEWAI'.",
    "NEWAI-'new artificial intelligence'-is my term for computers based on neural nets and comprising deep learning together with large language models, both of which have been hugely successful in recent years.",
    "NEWAI in its deep learning form, is the undisputed champion at games with exhaustively defined rules, such as chess.",
    "In such cases a deep learning machine can acquire, in a day or two, the ability to beat anyone by playing millions of games against itself and noting the moves that eventually lead to victory."
  ]
}